WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.458
♪ La-la-la-la, la-la-la-la ♪

00:08.541 --> 00:09.916
-[grunts]
-Mmm.

00:11.000 --> 00:14.708
[Wammawink] ♪ In Centaurworld ♪

00:14.791 --> 00:17.375
-[neighing]
-[vocalizing]

00:17.458 --> 00:18.583
[squeaks]

00:21.375 --> 00:24.791
Ow! [whimpering] Ow!

00:24.875 --> 00:26.458
-[grunting]
-[squawking]

00:26.541 --> 00:27.875
Don't do that! [grunts]

00:28.583 --> 00:30.458
[whalesong]

00:31.083 --> 00:32.166
[yelps]

00:32.250 --> 00:34.125
Freedom!

00:35.250 --> 00:36.250
[grunts]

00:40.625 --> 00:42.666
Thanks for the ride. [chuckles]

00:42.750 --> 00:45.666
[Whaletaur] Thanks for trusting
I wouldn't digest your memories

00:45.750 --> 00:48.625
-while you were inside me.
-Wait. Who are you again?

00:49.458 --> 00:51.458
-Ha! Just kidding.
-[Centaurs laugh]

00:51.541 --> 00:53.375
Ched said something funny.

00:53.458 --> 00:54.833
What did you do to him?

00:54.916 --> 00:58.791
-Want a hand getting back in that water?
-[Whaletaur] No, I'm good.

00:58.875 --> 01:03.083
Just, you know, please go.
It's easier when no one's looking at me.

01:04.166 --> 01:06.166
[grunting]

01:09.916 --> 01:11.541
[panting]

01:13.125 --> 01:14.541
[grunts]

01:14.625 --> 01:16.833
[ethereal music playing]

01:22.541 --> 01:24.083
[high-pitched ringing]

01:24.166 --> 01:26.375
-Well, we're here. [laughs]
-[snorts]

01:26.458 --> 01:29.166
Let's take a moment
to consider how far we've--

01:29.250 --> 01:31.125
[Whaletaur grunting]

01:33.333 --> 01:35.125
To consider how far we've--

01:35.208 --> 01:37.083
[grunting]

01:38.333 --> 01:40.833
-To consider how far we've--
-[loud splash]

01:41.708 --> 01:44.208
[Whaletaur] Made it! I'm good, guys.

01:44.291 --> 01:46.750
-To consider how far we've--
-Where's Waterbaby?

01:46.833 --> 01:50.375
She said she was gonna give us the last
piece of the key, so where is she?

01:50.458 --> 01:51.583
Are you kidding me?

01:51.666 --> 01:54.750
Tell me somebody worked out a system
for letting her know we're here.

01:54.833 --> 01:57.583
-[high-pitched ringing]
-Dude, can you shut that thing off?

01:57.666 --> 01:58.750
[screams, gasps]

01:59.375 --> 02:00.625
My nuggets!

02:03.500 --> 02:05.750
-[rumbling]
-[all] Oh!

02:09.041 --> 02:11.250
-[whooshing]
-[chittering]

02:11.333 --> 02:14.541
Oh-ho-ho! That should get
Waterbaby's attention.

02:14.625 --> 02:16.833
-[grunting]
-[Ched grunting]

02:17.958 --> 02:19.083
[groaning]

02:19.166 --> 02:21.250
Okay. So, now what?

02:21.333 --> 02:24.000
Well, we, we, we, we wait.

02:24.083 --> 02:25.416
We wait for Waterbaby,

02:25.500 --> 02:28.083
and we enjoy what time…

02:28.166 --> 02:31.666
what little… [laughs] little time
we have left with you-- Horse!

02:31.750 --> 02:33.208
[snoring]

02:34.750 --> 02:38.916
She's sleeping? What--
How could she sleep at a moment like this?

02:39.000 --> 02:41.875
Well, yeah. I mean, she's super tired.

02:41.958 --> 02:44.083
And think about all the travelin'
and singin'

02:44.166 --> 02:46.250
and wild stuff we've been doin'.

02:46.333 --> 02:48.541
Her body changed, even. It's crazy.

02:48.625 --> 02:52.833
She probably wants to be all rested
before she meets her actual best friend.

02:52.916 --> 02:54.250
Hoo-whee!

02:54.333 --> 02:56.375
This must really suck for you.

02:56.458 --> 02:58.041
I mean, I would be a hot mess

02:58.125 --> 03:01.750
if my buddy for fancy frolicking
was to walk into that Rift

03:01.833 --> 03:03.625
and go back to her old life.

03:03.708 --> 03:05.333
Then I was never gonna ever see

03:05.416 --> 03:08.666
her perfect hair
balled up in scrunchies ever again.

03:08.750 --> 03:10.291
Wait. I--

03:10.375 --> 03:12.541
Ever, ever never again.

03:13.083 --> 03:15.166
Wammawink, in your whole life!

03:15.250 --> 03:16.416
Until you die.

03:18.291 --> 03:19.708
And even after you die.

03:20.250 --> 03:21.250
Also.

03:21.875 --> 03:24.750
-You're a great friend.
-[quavering]

03:25.333 --> 03:26.291
Horse! Get up!

03:26.375 --> 03:28.375
[laughing hysterically]

03:29.125 --> 03:30.083
[snorts]

03:30.166 --> 03:35.583
According to the rules of Centaurworld
outlined in this ancient scripture,

03:35.666 --> 03:37.833
we have a lot to do before you go.

03:37.916 --> 03:40.875
-Uh, what?
-Number one. Reflections.

03:40.958 --> 03:43.583
-Ooh!
-We reflect on our time together.

03:43.666 --> 03:45.208
[grunts] Hard pass.

03:46.833 --> 03:48.458
Ooh!

03:49.000 --> 03:53.583
I have a short poem
I would like to recite for Horse.

03:53.666 --> 03:54.916
[chuckling] Ooh!

03:55.000 --> 03:57.708
There once was a Centaur named Wenis

03:57.791 --> 04:01.750
Okay. That's time. [laughs]
Ched, would you like to go next?

04:01.833 --> 04:05.750
Once upon a time, a horse showed up.
We all had to deal with horse stink.

04:05.833 --> 04:08.333
Ched had a lot of great ideas,
but everybody ignored him

04:08.416 --> 04:10.500
'cause their brains were soft
from horse fumes.

04:10.583 --> 04:13.291
Bunch of times we almost died,
but didn't 'cause she was there.

04:13.375 --> 04:14.416
That's cool. Whatever.

04:14.500 --> 04:16.416
Just like all horses, Horse was gross,

04:16.500 --> 04:18.333
lousy, and really bad at stuff.

04:18.416 --> 04:21.083
You know what? Whatever.
Horse was a great friend.

04:21.166 --> 04:24.583
And… And a hero.
And a beacon of unflagging integrity.

04:24.666 --> 04:29.375
-And you know what? I hate this game!
-Ah! Thank you, Ched. That was beautiful.

04:29.458 --> 04:30.708
Who's next?

04:30.791 --> 04:32.416
Oh, oh, oh, me. Me, me, me.

04:32.958 --> 04:37.208
I've prepared a presentation
in anticipation of this moment. [inhales]

04:37.291 --> 04:39.583
Time's kind of tight, Zulius.

04:39.666 --> 04:42.416
Can we watch
your little slideshow after Horse is gone?

04:42.500 --> 04:44.500
"My little slideshow"?

04:44.583 --> 04:46.083
How dare you?

04:46.166 --> 04:47.958
Ah! Virgin mojito.

04:49.083 --> 04:50.083
I'm leaving!

04:52.291 --> 04:55.166
[cackles] I'm back.
I can't leave you. Hello.

04:55.250 --> 04:58.458
Okay. Well,
that was very on-brand, Zulius.

04:58.541 --> 04:59.875
Glendale?

04:59.958 --> 05:05.666
I think I could sum up our journey
chronologically with my tummy stuff.

05:05.750 --> 05:09.958
♪ I'd like to show you my collection ♪

05:10.833 --> 05:14.083
♪ These shiny things I kinda stole ♪

05:14.166 --> 05:15.291
Mm, don't tell now.

05:15.375 --> 05:19.041
♪ Tchotchkes from every direction ♪

05:19.125 --> 05:24.541
♪ I stole them
And I put them in my tummy hole ♪

05:26.083 --> 05:28.000
Hey! You know what else I stole?

05:28.083 --> 05:32.291
I stole this song!
Yeah, I done stole it from the Beartaur!

05:32.375 --> 05:33.666
Fortune cookie!

05:34.833 --> 05:38.166
"A close friend
will soon become a father."

05:38.250 --> 05:40.250
[gasps] Wow.

05:40.333 --> 05:42.208
I'm going to be a baby!

05:44.083 --> 05:46.791
Can Waterbaby's houseboat
even fit through there?

05:46.875 --> 05:48.416
My turn! Okay. [chuckles]

05:48.500 --> 05:51.166
I was going to sing a song, but it's fine.

05:51.250 --> 05:55.416
Should've prepared a backup, but…
No. You know what? Two songs is fine.

05:55.500 --> 05:56.875
Mine will be different.

05:57.666 --> 06:00.916
Goodbye, Horsey.
Here is a song I made. It's for you.

06:01.000 --> 06:02.125
[floor squeaking]

06:02.750 --> 06:06.625
This is the story of Comfortable Doug,

06:06.708 --> 06:09.291
hero of his own life, rhyme, and verse.

06:09.375 --> 06:13.625
And now he can talk about himself
in the third person.

06:14.333 --> 06:18.583
Come forth and give love
to Comfortable Doug.

06:19.166 --> 06:20.250
That's me.

06:20.333 --> 06:23.416
♪ When I look back upon the story
Of my life ♪

06:23.500 --> 06:25.583
-♪ Life ♪
-♪ I find I'm not a hero ♪

06:25.666 --> 06:29.000
-♪ I'm the best supporting actor ♪
-♪ Actor ♪

06:29.083 --> 06:32.083
-♪ I never found a husband or a wife ♪
-♪ Wife ♪

06:32.166 --> 06:36.333
♪ Never found a thing to love
Or something to go after ♪

06:36.416 --> 06:37.458
-♪ After ♪
-[whimpering]

06:37.541 --> 06:41.750
♪ My life, it was no fairy tale
As a night guard in the Moletaur jail ♪

06:41.833 --> 06:43.041
♪ Jail ♪

06:43.125 --> 06:45.666
♪ But then I came above ground ♪

06:45.750 --> 06:47.750
-♪ To feel the sun ♪
-♪ So bright ♪

06:47.833 --> 06:51.333
♪ I won the sash
In Johnny Teatime's Be Best Competition ♪

06:51.416 --> 06:53.791
-♪ First place ♪
-♪ I can't return to prison life ♪

06:53.875 --> 06:56.041
-♪ With the earthworms, the bugs ♪
-♪ So nasty ♪

06:56.125 --> 07:00.041
♪ I'm the hero of my story now
I'm Comfortable Doug ♪

07:00.125 --> 07:02.125
♪ I'm Comfortable Doug ♪

07:02.666 --> 07:04.166
♪ Comfortable Doug ♪

07:04.250 --> 07:08.375
♪ I'm Comfortable
Comfortable, Comfortable Doug ♪

07:08.458 --> 07:10.958
♪ I'm Comfortable Doug ♪

07:11.041 --> 07:12.541
♪ Comfortable Doug ♪

07:12.625 --> 07:16.583
♪ I'm Comfortable
Comfortable, Comfortable Doug ♪

07:17.458 --> 07:18.375
♪ Yes ♪

07:18.458 --> 07:23.250
You know,
I've always been called Comfortable Doug.

07:24.041 --> 07:27.625
Because that's my name.

07:27.708 --> 07:31.791
But recently, I became Comfortable Doug.

07:32.708 --> 07:36.208
And I want to share with you all

07:36.291 --> 07:39.500
that you could be comfortable as well.

07:40.291 --> 07:42.708
Just ask the Glitter Cats. Glitter Cats.

07:42.791 --> 07:44.833
-[both] Yes?
-Are you comfortable?

07:44.916 --> 07:46.833
[both] Yes, we're comfortable.

07:46.916 --> 07:48.750
[Wammawink] What are they doing here?

07:48.833 --> 07:52.458
Doug, we're trying to have
some alone time with Horse before--

07:52.541 --> 07:56.125
Or just ask Sunfish Merguy.
Sunfish Merguy.

07:56.208 --> 07:57.875
-Yeah?
-Are you comfortable?

07:57.958 --> 07:59.916
Yeah. Fairly comfortable, thanks.

08:00.416 --> 08:02.500
-[grunts]
-Or just ask Gebbrey.

08:02.583 --> 08:03.916
-Gebbrey.
-Uh?

08:04.000 --> 08:09.375
I know life is hard as a vegetable.
But are you comfortable?

08:09.458 --> 08:11.666
I'm not a vegetable. I'm a tree.

08:11.750 --> 08:14.041
And I'm not comfortable. I'm cold.

08:14.125 --> 08:18.583
Well, if you had a jacket,
you would be otherwise?

08:18.666 --> 08:21.208
Okay, look.
Don't get weird on me with details.

08:21.291 --> 08:28.250
My point is, none of us are comfortable
until we are all comfortable. And I'm…

08:28.333 --> 08:31.708
[all] ♪ Comfortable
Comfortable, Comfortable Doug ♪

08:31.791 --> 08:36.041
♪ I'm Comfortable Doug
Comfortable Doug ♪

08:36.125 --> 08:38.625
♪ I'm Comfortable, Comfortable ♪

08:38.708 --> 08:41.458
♪ Comfortable Doug
Yeah ♪

08:43.375 --> 08:45.875
Are you some sort of god?

08:45.958 --> 08:48.625
No, I am not, fart neck.

08:48.708 --> 08:49.791
Am I?

08:50.916 --> 08:52.291
Be comfortable.

08:59.458 --> 09:01.583
You know what's really comfortable?

09:01.666 --> 09:03.041
Footie pajamas!

09:03.125 --> 09:05.833
Which we will now knit
for Horse as a group.

09:05.916 --> 09:08.750
That way,
she'll remember us whenever she sleeps.

09:08.833 --> 09:12.708
[chuckles nervously] Well, footie pajamas
aren't super practical in wartime.

09:12.791 --> 09:15.083
It's settled, then! Herd, assemble!

09:16.500 --> 09:18.625
[whimpering]

09:18.708 --> 09:20.250
Wait. Are we really doing this?

09:20.333 --> 09:21.875
[suspenseful music playing]

09:23.000 --> 09:24.708
[Horse grunting]

09:26.666 --> 09:30.250
[laughing] You know,
knitting is just like friendship.

09:30.333 --> 09:32.750
There's no mistake you can't fix. [laughs]

09:32.833 --> 09:35.583
You just jab stuff with needles
until you're happy.

09:35.666 --> 09:38.208
And if you do it right,
it never leaves you.

09:38.291 --> 09:41.541
-Hello!
-[pompous music playing]

09:41.625 --> 09:43.000
So sorry I'm late.

09:43.083 --> 09:44.625
-[beeps]
-[loud splash]

09:45.666 --> 09:47.375
Waterbaby!

09:47.458 --> 09:51.500
We were just bonding by trapping--
Knitting Horse into these pajamas.

09:51.583 --> 09:52.916
[laughs, grunts]

09:53.000 --> 09:54.583
-Wanna help?
-Oh no, no.

09:54.666 --> 09:56.541
Sweetheart, there's no time.

09:56.625 --> 09:59.000
We gotta get
this baby girl through the Rift.

09:59.083 --> 10:01.041
Only I call her that.

10:01.916 --> 10:05.500
-Okay, okay. Horse.
-Mm-hmm?

10:05.583 --> 10:08.083
Hand me the thing.
We don't have much time.

10:11.125 --> 10:12.666
[whimpering, grunts]

10:12.750 --> 10:15.625
Um, fine. If we can't finish the PJs,

10:15.708 --> 10:19.750
we can at least sing our traditional
Centaurworld before-you-go song.

10:19.833 --> 10:23.125
It's basically mandatory
for when we see someone off.

10:23.208 --> 10:25.208
I don't remember that song.

10:25.291 --> 10:27.500
Well, no one's ever left us before!

10:28.041 --> 10:29.416
[squeals, laughs]

10:29.500 --> 10:33.333
♪ This will take just a minute
This will only take second of your time ♪

10:33.416 --> 10:35.666
♪ I see you're heading out
But need I remind you ♪

10:35.750 --> 10:38.791
♪ That we haven't technically
Said goodbye yet ♪

10:38.875 --> 10:40.458
♪ Just wait for a moment ♪

10:40.541 --> 10:42.750
♪ Centaurworld has rules
By which we must abide ♪

10:42.833 --> 10:46.500
♪ Things to do before you leave our side
Like magicking a bunch of tiny teapots ♪

10:46.583 --> 10:49.000
♪ 'Cause teapots are a thing
Everybody needs, right? ♪

10:49.083 --> 10:52.500
♪ Oh, before you go ♪

10:52.583 --> 10:53.916
♪ You kind of owe ♪

10:54.000 --> 10:57.916
♪ A bit of quality time with friends
Who likely won't see you again ♪

10:58.000 --> 10:58.833
But I--

10:58.916 --> 11:01.250
♪ Oh, before you go ♪

11:01.833 --> 11:03.958
♪ There are a few traditions
Bobs and bits ♪

11:04.041 --> 11:05.875
♪ And kindnesses to show, like… ♪

11:05.958 --> 11:08.000
-Like?
-[laughs] Yes!

11:08.083 --> 11:09.708
Yes. Like, uh… [gasps]

11:09.791 --> 11:12.666
♪ Farewell toasts in secret places
All while making tiny faces ♪

11:12.750 --> 11:14.875
♪ Catch Fishtaurs in the stream
Using Ched as bait ♪

11:14.958 --> 11:15.875
I didn't agree to this.

11:15.958 --> 11:18.625
♪ Choreograph friendship dances
Group crochets, bye prances ♪

11:18.708 --> 11:21.041
♪ Sewing tiny hats
While journaling our dreams ♪

11:21.125 --> 11:22.333
Wammawink, I gotta go.

11:22.416 --> 11:24.833
-Yeah, but there's, like, more.
-Oh.

11:24.916 --> 11:27.875
♪ Decorating Gigglecakes
Magicking a jelly lake ♪

11:27.958 --> 11:29.750
♪ Something-- Whatever ♪

11:29.833 --> 11:32.791
♪ We make burnt offerings to Trebbor ♪

11:32.875 --> 11:34.541
-Who's he?
-A friend or something.

11:34.625 --> 11:41.500
♪ Then we shoot tiny versions of ourselves
From our hooves ♪

11:41.583 --> 11:43.583
Okay, I'm gonna start walkin' this way.

11:43.666 --> 11:46.583
♪ And so ♪

11:46.666 --> 11:51.125
♪ Before you go
Just thought you ought to know ♪

11:51.208 --> 11:53.958
♪ That some of us have not accepted
You're leaving ♪

11:54.041 --> 11:57.958
♪ And they're not prepared for grieving ♪

11:59.000 --> 12:00.208
[sighs]

12:00.750 --> 12:03.291
I am going to miss you so much, Horse.

12:05.000 --> 12:06.291
I know.

12:06.375 --> 12:07.791
I'm gonna miss you, too.

12:08.958 --> 12:11.500
[tiny Wammawinks screaming]

12:12.750 --> 12:13.750
All of you.

12:15.291 --> 12:18.625
I never would've made it here
if it wasn't for this herd.

12:18.708 --> 12:21.666
Thank you for everything
you've done for me.

12:21.750 --> 12:24.541
-But especially you.
-It was nothin', baby girl.

12:24.625 --> 12:27.250
-No, it was a ton-- It was a lot.
-[whimpering]

12:27.333 --> 12:30.375
-I've gotta agree with Ched on this one.
-Finally.

12:30.458 --> 12:32.166
Hey, group hug!

12:32.750 --> 12:35.750
I wish we could make
this moment last forever.

12:35.833 --> 12:37.291
All right. Break it up!

12:37.375 --> 12:39.916
It's time to let Horse
complete her journey.

12:40.000 --> 12:43.791
Everyone, step back a few feet.
This might get weird.

12:43.875 --> 12:45.208
[whooshing]

12:46.125 --> 12:48.208
♪ Follow the road ♪

12:49.125 --> 12:51.916
♪ Commune with the Shamans ♪

12:52.000 --> 12:54.583
♪ Convince each one
Of what needs to be done ♪

12:54.666 --> 12:58.333
♪ And each shard
That they guard will be yours ♪

12:58.416 --> 13:03.416
♪ The fragments required
To open dimensional doors ♪

13:04.833 --> 13:10.875
♪ At the rifts between the worlds
I will meet you ♪

13:11.875 --> 13:13.625
♪ To form ♪

13:15.375 --> 13:22.083
♪ The key ♪

13:22.166 --> 13:24.541
[whooshing]

13:25.333 --> 13:27.416
[whooshing]

13:32.000 --> 13:33.375
Ready?

13:34.250 --> 13:37.791
Remember to let us know
that you made it through in one piece!

13:39.750 --> 13:42.500
[sweeping orchestral music playing]

13:46.916 --> 13:48.083
[squeaking]

13:48.166 --> 13:50.125
[grunting]

13:51.500 --> 13:53.041
[grunting]

13:53.125 --> 13:54.291
[whimpers]

13:54.375 --> 13:58.791
Oh no! She's going to land
on the other side completely nude!

13:58.875 --> 14:01.583
Ha-ha! Nude. Naked Horse butt.

14:02.416 --> 14:04.250
[whooshing]

14:11.250 --> 14:12.375
Hello?

14:15.166 --> 14:16.416
Hello?

14:17.416 --> 14:18.916
[whooshing]

14:21.250 --> 14:22.250
Huh?

14:25.708 --> 14:28.125
Rider! [panting]

14:29.083 --> 14:30.708
[snarling]

14:32.166 --> 14:33.166
[roars]

14:33.250 --> 14:34.583
[gasps]

14:35.875 --> 14:37.250
[panting]

14:38.750 --> 14:39.916
Rider?

14:40.000 --> 14:41.916
[gentle music playing]

14:42.000 --> 14:43.000
Rider?

14:43.083 --> 14:45.125
[panting] Rider!

14:46.041 --> 14:47.625
[laughs] Rider!

14:48.208 --> 14:49.583
Uh--

14:50.458 --> 14:51.666
Rider, it's me.

15:01.375 --> 15:03.041
♪ You're okay ♪

15:04.791 --> 15:06.750
♪ You're all right ♪

15:08.416 --> 15:11.875
♪ I'll never ever leave your side ♪

15:14.166 --> 15:15.708
♪ I will stay ♪

15:17.791 --> 15:18.916
♪ I will fight ♪

15:20.875 --> 15:21.875
[sighs]

15:24.916 --> 15:28.708
♪ With you ♪

15:29.958 --> 15:31.541
[joyful music playing]

15:40.583 --> 15:42.291
♪ It's you
It's really you ♪

15:42.375 --> 15:45.583
♪ I can't believe it
There's so much I wanna say ♪

15:45.666 --> 15:47.208
♪ Too much I--
Oh, by the way ♪

15:47.291 --> 15:49.458
♪ I talk now
That's something new ♪

15:49.541 --> 15:53.250
♪ That's something we will get to later
But first ♪

15:53.875 --> 15:56.916
♪ Let me just enjoy this moment ♪

15:57.000 --> 15:59.791
♪ When meeting in the middle ♪

16:01.416 --> 16:03.291
♪ It's you
It's really you ♪

16:03.375 --> 16:05.916
♪ Despite the changes
I would know you anywhere ♪

16:06.000 --> 16:08.916
♪ The voice, the face, the hair
Might all be different ♪

16:09.000 --> 16:10.208
♪ But you're still you ♪

16:10.291 --> 16:14.083
♪ And all I wanna do is
Hold you close again ♪

16:14.166 --> 16:19.916
[both] ♪ I have journeyed from so far
To meet you in the middle ♪

16:23.791 --> 16:25.833
♪ 'Cause I've been searching for you ♪

16:25.916 --> 16:29.791
♪ And I was so afraid
That I would lose my place ♪

16:29.875 --> 16:33.666
♪ And our memories would fade
Or you'd move on somehow ♪

16:33.750 --> 16:38.041
♪ And I'd lose my closest family ♪

16:40.041 --> 16:42.625
-♪ I have been searching ♪
-♪ I have been searching ♪

16:42.708 --> 16:48.666
[both] ♪ And I knew
That you were searching for me ♪

16:48.750 --> 16:55.375
♪ I wondered
What if I forget your face? ♪

16:56.750 --> 17:03.750
♪ I know
And what if you move on without me? ♪

17:06.125 --> 17:08.833
[both] ♪ What if I found the way back ♪

17:10.708 --> 17:11.750
[sighs]

17:11.833 --> 17:14.416
♪ But you weren't there? ♪

17:18.625 --> 17:21.041
-♪ It's you ♪
-♪ It's really you ♪

17:21.125 --> 17:24.958
♪ Feels like I'm dreaming
But now finally you're here ♪ [sniffles]

17:25.041 --> 17:28.916
♪ I never ever wanna
See you disappear again ♪

17:29.000 --> 17:30.708
♪ Now that you're near to me ♪

17:30.791 --> 17:36.416
[both] ♪ I promise
That I'll never let you go ♪

17:40.791 --> 17:45.000
Horse, I can't believe it! I mean, I--
Gosh, I have a million questions.

17:45.083 --> 17:48.416
And you have so many of those-- So many.

17:48.500 --> 17:51.916
-What are these?
-I'll explain. I'll explain everything.

17:52.000 --> 17:54.250
You're right. Yes. Let's get you home.

17:57.791 --> 17:58.916
Whoa.

17:59.000 --> 18:01.208
How did you find this place?

18:01.291 --> 18:05.833
When I was captured by the Minotaurs,
I was held prisoner at a camp near here.

18:06.291 --> 18:10.333
I escaped, took them all out,
and chased the last guard into the portal.

18:10.416 --> 18:11.666
Then I found you.

18:15.458 --> 18:17.875
It's like fate
brought us back together again.

18:17.958 --> 18:19.500
[solemn music playing]

18:21.125 --> 18:22.916
[bird cawing]

18:23.000 --> 18:24.208
Wow.

18:24.791 --> 18:27.041
I forgot how bad it is here.

18:28.333 --> 18:30.458
So much devastation.

18:31.916 --> 18:35.500
Now that you're back,
we can bring the Artifact to the General.

18:35.583 --> 18:38.541
[sighs] I don't have it.
It's back in Centaurworld.

18:38.625 --> 18:40.666
Centaurworld?

18:40.750 --> 18:44.250
Oh no! I was supposed
to let Wammawink know that I made it here!

18:44.333 --> 18:45.166
Wamma-what?

18:45.250 --> 18:48.458
I promised my friends I'd pop my head
through the Rift for a second

18:48.541 --> 18:49.958
to tell them I made it through.

18:50.041 --> 18:51.041
Your friends?

18:51.125 --> 18:52.916
I'll explain on the way.

18:53.000 --> 18:55.333
Oh no. They're probably really worried.

18:56.583 --> 18:57.958
Well, she's fine. Let's go.

18:58.041 --> 19:01.666
I got a sports massage in half an hour.
Jeffica said she could get the knots out.

19:01.750 --> 19:05.583
No, Ched. We're waiting for Horse
to let us know that she made it.

19:06.250 --> 19:08.375
Did you say Jeffica?

19:09.583 --> 19:12.333
But how can you tell
if a bird face is handsome?

19:12.416 --> 19:15.958
Ched's not a bird. He's a Birdtaur.
And the handsome face was a human face.

19:16.041 --> 19:18.666
-That part is clear, right?
-No part of that was clear.

19:18.750 --> 19:22.708
Don't worry, toots.
It'll all make sense in the end.

19:22.791 --> 19:23.958
[plays drums]

19:24.041 --> 19:26.666
I don't know why
I felt compelled to do that.

19:27.166 --> 19:28.583
Also, my tail talks now.

19:28.666 --> 19:31.750
But it doesn't say what I think.
It just tells jokes. [chuckles]

19:31.833 --> 19:34.125
-[whooshing]
-[gasps] Ahh!

19:34.208 --> 19:35.500
Maybe we should go back.

19:35.583 --> 19:37.208
I haven't told them I'm okay.

19:37.291 --> 19:40.000
They wouldn't lock the door
unless something was wrong.

19:44.375 --> 19:46.291
[dramatic music playing]

19:48.083 --> 19:50.791
Did you just snap shut
this world's only butt flap

19:50.875 --> 19:52.375
to the Bummer Dimension?

19:52.458 --> 19:54.291
I did what I had to do.

19:55.541 --> 19:56.916
My magic isn't working.

19:57.000 --> 19:58.625
You can have the key.

19:58.708 --> 20:02.125
They just wanna make sure their friend
made it through. Open the door.

20:04.208 --> 20:05.916
[panting, grunting]

20:06.791 --> 20:09.916
-Where is it?
-Horse, the other one's closed, too.

20:10.000 --> 20:10.958
What?

20:13.291 --> 20:14.791
Just open the door.

20:14.875 --> 20:18.458
How can you say that?
Do you understand what you're suggesting?

20:23.000 --> 20:24.375
Please, listen.

20:24.458 --> 20:26.416
You know what is locked in there.

20:26.500 --> 20:27.958
Yeah, Horse.

20:28.041 --> 20:30.000
An unspeakable evil.

20:30.083 --> 20:32.625
Yeah, Horse. And we wanna know she's okay.

20:32.708 --> 20:35.458
I mean, they do.
I don't really care. But tell us.

20:35.541 --> 20:38.208
What if she didn't make it
to the other side?

20:38.291 --> 20:40.250
One horse is a small price to pay.

20:41.041 --> 20:44.916
If he is freed, he will not rest
until both worlds are destroyed.

20:45.625 --> 20:46.625
I'm sorry.

20:48.875 --> 20:50.333
[panting, grunting]

20:51.041 --> 20:52.791
-We're trapped in here.
-[snarling]

20:52.875 --> 20:53.916
What is that?

21:00.125 --> 21:03.875
[eerie voices] ♪ Hush now
Hide, all you little ones ♪

21:03.958 --> 21:09.083
♪ Rush now
Into the middle of nowhere ♪

21:09.166 --> 21:12.583
♪ Singing and laughter will die ♪

21:14.500 --> 21:20.916
♪ Dreamless sleep
Follows the Nowhere King ♪

21:21.000 --> 21:26.500
♪ When his kingdom comes
Darkness is nigh ♪

21:26.583 --> 21:28.500
-[snarls]
-[Horse gasps]

21:28.583 --> 21:32.125
♪ Quiet
Crawl through the in-between ♪

21:32.208 --> 21:38.666
♪ Silent
Secretive feeling of fearsome hatred ♪

21:38.750 --> 21:41.750
♪ That reaches the skies ♪

21:43.375 --> 21:49.583
♪ You will bring joy to the Nowhere King ♪

21:50.166 --> 21:53.625
-♪ When he sees the light ♪
-[retches]

21:53.708 --> 21:57.541
♪ Leaving your eyes ♪

21:59.625 --> 22:02.166
[snarling]

22:02.250 --> 22:03.375
You…

22:06.875 --> 22:08.875
[ominous music playing]
